msDesc.head: Nicholas of Lyra, Commentaries on Matthew and John

p.note: The right flyleaf is foliated and consists of a leaf with random glosses by the same hand as the main text.

supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil. regna mundi

collation.catchwords: Catchwords in brown ink, missing on quires 7 and 9.

supportDesc.condition: torn or cut, only about half of it remains. This leaf was probably originally part of the textblock. is glued to the right cover.

p.note: Top left corner, National Library book label; upper part of page in ink by a medieval hand: attinet(page, inlcuding first words, cropped); in brown ink by a modern hand: Tillhör Bernhard Rosenblad; below, by the same hand: Köpt i December 1830 i Leipzig för 3 Rles? 16 fr. Conv. Mynt utom Kostnader.

binding.p: Medieval binding. Red leather over wooden boards. Spine painted grey. 4 double raised bands and endbands. , in black ink or paint: Nicol. de Lyra.; in lead: M8?; stamped in gold: A 157; in red paint on a dark grey background: A.
binding.decoNote: Simple painted decoration consisting of a panel with an x-shape inside on both covers.
binding.condition: Cover extremely worn. The colour of the leather is heavily faded. There are multiple worm holes and abrasions on the covers. Holes from corner and centre pieces on and , the latter also has holes after straps. Upper part of , remnats of label with part of a letter visible. The boards are exposed on all sides. On two of the attachment straps are visible. On the centre and upper left corner of the a parchment fragment from an older manuscript is visible through large gaps in the leather. The has been painted grey at a later date.

history.provenance: Origin and early provenance unknown. Purchased by Bernhard Rosenblad in Leipzig in . Purchased from him by G. J. R. Gordon.
history.acquisition: Purchased from G. J. R. Gordon by the Royal Library in .

msItem.title: Commentaries on Matthew and John
Prologue
msItem.incipit: QUatuor facies vni et cetera Ezechiel primo secundum quod scribit beatus gregorius
msItem.explicit: uel faciebus significabantur iiiior ewangeliste et sic patet textus

msItem.title: Commentary on Matthew
msItem.incipit: Liber generacionis ihesu christi Ewangelium mathei diuiditur in duas partes
msItem.explicit: ut sic non deficiet fides petri Ad laudem et gloriam domini nostri ihesu christi Qui est honor et gloria in secula seculorum AMEN
msItem.finalRubric: Explicit Postilla super Matheum Edita a fratre Nycolao de Lyra de ordine fratrum Mynorum deo gracias amen

msItem.title: Prologue
msItem.incipit: FAcies aquile desuper ipsorum quatuor ezechieli id est ezechiel propheta cui aperti
msItem.explicit: doctrina quia paratus est reuelare veritatem fideliter inquirentibus ipsam

msItem.title: Commentary on John
msItem.incipit: IN principio erat verbum sed quod patet ex predictis intencio beati Iohannis est
msItem.explicit: id est audiebat ita quod ibi accipitur uisus pro auditu
msItem.note: The text ends in the middle of a gloss on John 20:27. is glued to the cover as a pastedown, the text on this leaf seems to consist of random glosses. The first gloss is on Mat. 5:21, further down on Mat. 4:17, followed by undidentified glosses.
There are no modern editions of these commentaries, but they were included in early prints of the Bible, e.g. Lyon 1545.

supportDesc.condition: The parchement is dirty, wrinkled, and torn in places. Holes in the parchment throughout, some of them with contemporary repairs, e.g. on . Cuts or tears in the parchment in some places, e.g. in the outer margin on . Leaves damaged by damp or spills here and there, especially on , where it partially affects the legibility of the text.

layout.note: Ruling and guidelines in ink. Pricking in the margins.

p.note: Scattered additions in ink by one or several medieval hands in the margins throughout. The additions consist of notes on the content, corrections, and manicules and nota marks. Throughout there are also notes in small letters in ink and pencil in the running titles. These are probably instructions to the rubricator.
In the lower margin there is a note that refers to for relevant content, on 9rb a note refers back to 1vb.

decoDesc.p: Main text in dark brown ink, capitals touched in red, rubrics in red and with red strike-through.
decoDesc.decoNote: , opening foliate initial Q over 6 lines. Letter in shades of green on gold and framed in pink. Counterspace filled with red and gold. The letter extends into the margins in a vegetative shape with leaves in green, yellow, blue, pink, and gold. , decorated initial F over 5 lines. The initial is similar to the opening initial, but smaller and without gold, except for in the counterspace. The body is painted in grey and purple, counterspace filled with red and gold, and the leaf shapes in green, blue, and yellow. , plain initials over 2-3 lines in red.
, diagram in brown and red ink showing the family tree of King David.
